bricscad dialect should report BricsCAD's sysvars, not AutoCAD's
================================================================

Summary
-------

`clautolisp --bricscad` answers GETVAR/SETVAR from the *AutoCAD-2026*
sysvar catalogue: every dialect returns identical sysvar data. A diff of

    sysvars-alfe-Darwin-bricscad.txt        (real BricsCAD V26, via alfe)
    sysvars-clautolisp-Darwin-bricscad.txt  (clautolisp --bricscad)

shows 798 of 1836 variables differ. They fall into a small number of
root-cause classes; this issue records the classification, fixes the
unambiguous class now (Phase 1), and tracks the rest as deferred work.

IMPORTANT caveat on the reference dump
--------------------------------------

sysvars-alfe-Darwin-bricscad.txt is ONE live, customised, French-locale
BricsCAD session with a metric drawing open and the user's profile/paths
loaded. It is authoritative for *which* variables exist and for dynamic
state, but NOT a clean factory-default reference for *values*: e.g.
INTERFERELAYER "Interférences", OVERKILLLAYER "Entités dupliquées",
DIMSTYLE "ISO-25", LOCALE "fr_FR", the SCHMS search paths. Do not bulk-
import values from it; re-harvest from a pristine profile + a freshly
created default drawing before adopting any static value (Phase 2).

Classification of the 798 differences
--------------------------------------

  474  alfe = nil, clautolisp non-nil
         BricsCAD does not define the variable; real GETVAR returns nil.
         clautolisp ships the AutoCAD catalogue value. -> Phase 1.
  174  genuine value disagreements (both sides non-nil, non-state)
         Some are real BricsCAD-vs-AutoCAD factory defaults; many are the
         loaded-drawing template / customised profile / locale. -> Phase 2,
         needs a clean re-harvest to separate the two.
   56  session / drawing / clock state
   31  machine paths
         DWGNAME, VIEWCTR, EXTMIN/EXTMAX, TD*, ACADPREFIX, *PATH … must
         stay dynamic/computed, never hardcoded. -> Phase 3 (compute) /
         keep-as-difference.
   25  colour-format representation ("White" / "RGB:.." vs "#ffffff")
   25  single-float print noise (0.01 vs 0.009999999776482582)
    9  doc-text placeholders (see below)
    4  radian-vs-degree (DIMJOGANG 0.785398 vs 45.0; POLARANG; LOFTANG1/2)
         clautolisp output/representation bugs, dialect-independent.
         -> separate issues (not bricscad-specific).

Decisions taken (per user, 2026-06-30)
--------------------------------------

- ACADVER / PROGRAM / VENDORNAME / PLATFORM / PRODUCT: KEEP clautolisp's
  own identity (stamped by APPLY-CLAUTOLISP-HOST-IDENTITY). A bricscad
  *dialect* is still the clautolisp engine; it must not masquerade as
  Bricsys. Not changed here.
- SYSCODEPAGE / DWGCODEPAGE: already implemented dynamically (launch
  encoding -> APPLY-LAUNCH-CODEPAGE-TO-SYSVARS) and DWG-driven. This is a
  *good* difference; keep it.
- DATE / CDATE / MILLISECS / ERRNO: already computed live; keep.
- All other host-derived state: keep dynamic; compute incrementally
  (Phase 3 list below).

Phase 1 — existence overlay (THIS CHANGE, 1.2.25)
-------------------------------------------------

Existence is locale-, profile-, platform- and drawing-independent, so it
is the one class adoptable from a single probe. New launch-time overlay
for the bricscad dialect drops the catalogue cells BricsCAD does not
define, so GETVAR returns nil and SETVAR signals :unknown-sysvar.

  - clautolisp/autolisp-mock-host/source/bricscad-sysvar-overrides.lisp
      *BRICSCAD-ABSENT-SYSVARS* (382 names) + APPLY-BRICSCAD-DIALECT-SYSVARS
  - host-undefine-sysvar generic (host / null-host / mock-host)
  - APPLY-DIALECT-SYSVAR-DEFAULTS wired into INSTALL-TRANSMIT-VARIABLES
    alongside the existing trust overlay, guarded on :bricscad-v26.

The 382 names are the INTERSECTION of two independent sources:
  (a) inventory :versions (… :bricscad nil)  — the portable spec marker;
  (b) the live BricsCAD V26 probe returning nil.
Agreement excludes the two residues below, both of which are left on the
catalogue value (conservative — never wrongly null a real BricsCAD var):

  - 39 inventory rows the V26 probe CONTRADICTS (inventory bug: BricsCAD
    *does* define them). Fix the inventory's :bricscad marker for:
      3DOSMODE BACTIONBARMODE BACTIONCOLOR BDEPENDENCYHIGHLIGHT
      BGRIPOBJCOLOR BGRIPOBJSIZE BLOCKTESTWINDOW BPARAMETERCOLOR
      BPARAMETERFONT BPARAMETERSIZE BPTEXTHORIZONTAL BTMARKDISPLAY
      CENTERMT CGEOCS CLIPROMPTUPDATE COMMANDPREVIEW DYNINFOTIPS
      GEOMAPMODE GRIPMULTIFUNCTIONAL GROUPDISPLAYMODE HPMAXLINES
      HPORIGINMODE HPQUICKPREVIEW INPUTSEARCHDELAY LAYEREVALCTL LISPSYS
      MTEXTAUTOSTACK NAVBARDISPLAY PDFSHX PLINEREVERSEWIDTHS PLOTROTMODE
      RIBBONSELECTMODE STARTMODE SUNSTATUS SUPPRESSALERTS
      VPLAYEROVERRIDESMODE VSFACESTYLE XREFTYPE _TOOLPALETTEPATH
  - 98 probe-nil rows the inventory still lists for BricsCAD (edition-/
    platform-specific absences, many Civil/BIM CV* and macOS-specific).
    Not nulled: they may exist on other BricsCAD builds.

Doc-text placeholders (the 9)
-----------------------------

These are catalogue values scraped verbatim from documentation, broken on
every dialect (not just bricscad):

  ACTIVITYINSIGHTSPATH "C:\\Users\\{username}\\…"   <- bricscad-absent;
       Phase 1 already makes --bricscad return nil for it.
  MENUNAME "customization_file_name"
  INETLOCATION "https://www.autodesk.com/autocad (AutoCAD), …"
  FONTMAP "acad.fmp (AutoCAD) or acadlt.fmp (AutoCAD LT)"
  POINTCLOUDCACHEFOLDER "C:\\Users\\%username%\\…"   (BMTOOLPATH similar)
  CMDLINEEDITBGCOLOR "RGB: 50 54 56 (Settings dialog) #323638 (Command line)"
  CMDLINEEDITFGCOLOR / REDHILITEFULL_EDGE_COLOR (same shape)

Resolution: these are mock-host catalogue defects, fixed by correcting the
inventory :default and regenerating sysvar-catalogue.lisp — deferred to
the mock host / catalogue-regen track, NOT special-cased per dialect. The
ones that are bricscad-absent (ACTIVITYINSIGHTSPATH) already resolve to
nil under --bricscad via Phase 1; MENUNAME / INETLOCATION / FONTMAP etc.
are bricscad-present and will get correct BricsCAD defaults during Phase 2.

Phase 3 — host-derived state not yet computed (deferred)
--------------------------------------------------------

114 host-derived variables currently return a static catalogue stand-in
where BricsCAD fills them dynamically. Computed today: DATE, CDATE,
MILLISECS, ERRNO, SYSCODEPAGE, DWGCODEPAGE, PROGRAM, VENDORNAME, PLATFORM,
ACADVER. NOT yet computed (representative, by sub-class):

  drawing/view geometry : EXTMIN EXTMAX VSMIN VSMAX LIMMAX VIEWCTR
                          VIEWSIZE GRIDUNIT SNAPUNIT
  window/screen         : SCREENSIZE SCREENBOXES SCREENMODE
                          WNDPMAIN WNDPTEXT WNDSTEXT
  drawing identity      : DWGPREFIX BASEFILE CLAYOUT WSCURRENT
  drawing timers        : TDCREATE TDUPDATE TDUCREATE TDUUPDATE
                          TDINDWG TDUSRTIMER
  command/session       : CMDACTIVE LASTPROMPT
  environment/identity  : LOGINNAME LOCALE  (OS-derivable)
  install/profile paths : ACADPREFIX SRCHPATH *PATH *PREFIX  (install-
                          specific; likely keep-as-difference, not compute)

Note: several entries the probe shows as "dynamic" are really metric-
template defaults captured because the alfe session had a drawing open
(DIMASZ 2.5, DIMTXT 2.5, INSUNITS 4, MEASUREMENT 1, TEXTSIZE 2.5,
the arrow lengths, DIMSTYLE "ISO-25"). Those belong to Phase 2's "default
new drawing" decision, not to live computation.

Acceptance (Phase 1)
--------------------

- (getvar "DYNPROMPT") => nil under --bricscad, unchanged under --autocad.
- (setvar "DYNPROMPT" 1) signals :unknown-sysvar under --bricscad.
- shared sysvars (OSMODE, CMDECHO, DIMSTYLE, SECURELOAD, …) intact.
- 382 cells removed; tests in sysvar-catalogue-tests.lisp.
- Re-run `make save-sysvars`; the --bricscad dump's nil-set grows by the
  382 confirmed-absent names.

Found by
--------

Manual diff of the alfe/clautolisp bricscad sysvar dumps, 2026-06-30.
Related: clautolisp-host-product-still-bricscad.issue (identity),
clautolisp-mock-host-getvar.issue (identity overlay).
